Safaricom has said it will recruit 62 interns by January 2017 as it progresses its agenda to woo more women to the technology field.The internships will target 40 female university students under its Women In Technology initiative, with a further 18 internships open to all university applicants and an additional four internships that will be filled through the Association for the Physically Disabled of Kenya. Our technology internship program is built on the knowledge that in order to continue transforming lives, we must continue to invest in building capacity to manage cutting edge technologies, director of technology Thibaud Rerolle said.